commText: Jaiswal and Buttler are at the crease. Jaiswal is on strike. Matt Henry will open the attack
Matt Henry to Jaiswal, 1 run, length ball angling across onto off stump. Punched to the left cover point for a single

Matt Henry to Buttler, byes, 1 run, a lovely inswinger from a length that made Ekana Stadium look like Seddon Park!! Totally cuts Buttler in half, between bat and body and Rahul can't gather cleanly as well with the swing. Batters get a bye
Matt Henry to Jaiswal, no run, fraction back of length and tight on off stump. Punched into the pitch back to Henry
Matt Henry to Jaiswal, SIX, 138.3 clicks, Henry errs by going fuller onto off stump, under the bat of Jaiswal and he latches under it to smoke it over long-on for a boundary
Matt Henry to Jaiswal, FOUR, six followed by a four!! A fearless hoist over extra cover as Henry persists with that fuller length, this time with a bit of width
Matt Henry to Jaiswal, 1 run, back of length and extra bounce onto off, Jaiswal controls his cut along the ground towards deep backward point
Mohsin Khan, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Mohsin Khan to Jaiswal, no run, fuller length with a bit of away movement from off. Hit into the ground towards mid-off
Mohsin Khan to Jaiswal, FOUR, 139.9 clicks, a length ball that shapes away and bounces devilishly from off stump. Catches a thick edge and goes between slip and short third for a boundary
Mohsin Khan to Jaiswal, 1 run, length ball outside off, punched towards the point region where QDK makes a diving stop to his right
Mohsin Khan to Buttler, no run, fuller length onto off stump, a solid defence from Buttler
Mohsin Khan to Buttler, 2 runs, length ball onto leg stump, clipped to the left of fine leg for a couple
LSG fielding coach Jonty Rhodes walks all the way across to give some words of encouragement to Badoni at third-man
Mohsin Khan to Buttler, no run, angling across beautifully from a length, beats Buttler on the outisde edge
Matt Henry to Jaiswal, no run, fuller length and shaping away from just outside off. Driven towards mid-off
Krunal Pandya back on the field. He seems to be moving fine
Matt Henry to Jaiswal, no run, angling across from a length, Jaiswal tried to run it down but the ball escaped past the bat
Matt Henry to Jaiswal, 1 run, hard length with a tight off stump line. Cut towards deep point
Matt Henry to Buttler, SIX, shuffles in for the ramp and connects it perfectly. This was a bit fuller and at the stumps, Buttler effortlessly scoops it over the fine leg boundary
Matt Henry to Buttler, no run, full and straight with a bit of tail back into the batter. Defended back towards Henry
Matt Henry to Buttler, 1 run, on a length and on the pads, clipped towards deep square
Mohsin Khan to Buttler, FOUR, pitched up onto off stump, Buttler drills it down the ground. To the left of Mohsin before he could stretch his arm wide.
Mohsin Khan to Buttler, 2 runs, on a length, punched in front of square as cover point dives over the ball
Mohsin Khan to Buttler, 1 run, fuller and angling in from round the wicket. Buttler shimmies inwards and tucks it to mid-wicket
Mohsin Khan to Jaiswal, 1 run, fuller delivery on off stump, Jaiswal with a push and run to mid-off
Mohsin Khan to Buttler, 1 run, pace off length ball outside off, Buttler early on the pull and inside halves it towards fine leg
Mohsin Khan to Jaiswal, no run, Jaiswal backed away and Mohsin followed him with a bouncer. The southpaw left it alone expecting a wide for height but the umpire happy to consider that legitimate
Matt Henry to Buttler, FOUR, too full and just outside off, Buttler snatches at it. Gets under it and hoists it over mid-on. One bounce and over
Matt Henry to Buttler, 3 runs, length ball angling in from a length. Punched uppishly but to the left of the cover fielder. The longer boundaries enable the first triple of the innings
Matt Henry to Jaiswal, no run, full outside off, goes under Jaiswal as he went for a big slog across the line

Matt Henry to Jaiswal, leg byes, 1 run, to point, Jaiswal premeditated a ramp over short fine but Henry bowled it quick and full outside off. The southpaw tried to adjust and ramp it over short third, but can't connect. Deflects off the pads for a single
Matt Henry to Buttler, FOUR, short ball onto the stumps, Buttler with a powerful pull shot behind square. Races away to the right of the fielder
Matt Henry to Buttler, 1 run, another short one to end the over, pulled into the ground towards deep square.
Yash Thakur, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Yash Thakur to Buttler, FOUR, too straight and full onto the boots. Clipped through square leg and goes between the umpire's legs for a boundary
Yash Thakur to Buttler, 1 run, 141.6 clicks, hard length and stump lined. Turned to the right of mid-on for a single
Yash Thakur to Jaiswal, FOUR, short and wide, Jaiswal says thank you very much and slashes it over the point fielder for a boundary
Yash Thakur to Jaiswal, 1 run, full and angling on the pads, pushed to the left of mid-on for a single
Yash Thakur to Buttler, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Yash Thakur to Buttler, out Bowled!! Knocked over! Yash Thakur with his arms aloft gladiator still. Roars in delight as the stadium echoes his emotion.I0$ A low full toss, was angling onto leg stump. Buttler shuffled a long way across and missed out on the clip. The slightest of bat on that one and it would have gone past short fine. Instead, the English skipper sees his leg stump pegged back. LSG strike with the penultimate ball of the powerplay. Buttler b Yash Thakur 34(18) [4s-4 6s-1]
Sanju Samson, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Yash Thakur to Samson, no run, good length and straight, Samson presents a full face in defence

Over Summary (1-6): -- Jaiswal hits Henry for a four and a six to get things started -- Mohsin bowls a decent first over -- Henry bowls an expensive over again -- Thakur traps Buttler -- RR score 60 in the powerplay
Marcus Stoinis, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Stoinis to Jaiswal, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Stoinis to Jaiswal, out Caught by Ravi Bishnoi!! Two wickets in three balls!! Stoinis strikes with his first delivery. A full delivery angling wide outside off. Jaiswal chases it and goes for a big slash. Ends up toe-ending it high in the air and Bishnoi from deep point settles nicely under it to complete the catch. I0$ Jaiswal c Ravi Bishnoi b Stoinis 24(18) [4s-3 6s-1]
Impact Sub: Riyan Parag comes in for Yuzi Chahal
Riyan Parag, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Stoinis to Riyan Parag, no run, 135 clicks, length ball angling onto off stump. Parag gets a bit of a thick edge towards backward point
Stoinis to Riyan Parag, 1 run, full on leg stump, driven down to long-on
Stoinis to Samson, 1 run, fuller on the pads, turned to deep mid-wicket
Stoinis to Riyan Parag, no run, good length and tight on off stump, punched back towards Stoinis
Stoinis to Riyan Parag, 1 run, good length and stump lined, punched down to long-on. Three runs and a wicket off this Stoinis over.
Jaiswal vs Stoinis in the IPL Runs: 18 Balls: 15 Dismissals: 3 Avg: 6 SR: 120
Krunal Pandya, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Krunal Pandya to Riyan Parag, 2 runs, gets it down to deep mid for a single as that was fired on to the pads. Quicker one and Riyan Parag kept it along the carpet
Krunal Pandya to Riyan Parag, 1 run, on the pads, easily put away to deep mid for a single
Krunal Pandya to Samson, 1 run, gets it down to deep mid for a single as the ball angled in
Krunal Pandya to Riyan Parag, 1 run, plays it down to long-on for a single as the ball slanted in again
Krunal Pandya to Samson, 1 run, quicker one, outside off the batter drives it wide of long-off for a single. Played an inside out along the carpet
Krunal Pandya to Riyan Parag, 1 run, quicker one, on the pads, nudged down to deep mid for a single
Mishy ji into the attack. He is the impact player for LSG. First game of the season for him.
Amit Mishra, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Mishra to Riyan Parag, 1 run, drops it flatter, Riyan Parag punches it down to long-on for a single
Mishra to Samson, 1 run, plays it down to long-off for a single. Played it off the back foot as that was bowled slower
Mishra to Riyan Parag, SIX, picked the bones out of that! Was dropped short, skidded on and Riyan Parag hung back to slam it wide of long-on. Huge hit
Mishra to Riyan Parag, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mishra to Riyan Parag, out Caught by Ayush Badoni!! The inspirational move has paid off. Mishra shows off his name by pointing to it. Parag has to go. He got greedy after the sixer and wanted to inside out but failed to find the gap. Hit it straight to the fielder. Was a loopy delivery well wide outside off and Riyan Parag fell for the bait. Mishra has preyed like that before and once again has another one. LSG turning this game around. Riyan Parag c Ayush Badoni b Mishra 14(11) [6s-1]
Mishra has been a stalwart in the IPL and has once again rubbed his magic on the game. He is just starting his spell.
Dhruv Jurel, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Mishra to Dhruv Jurel, no run, tossed up delivery, outside off, Dhruv Jurel gets a stride out and stabs it down to short third man
Mishra to Dhruv Jurel, no run, well lobbed up delivery and Dhruv Jurel slams the drive on the up to find the man at cover
Krunal Pandya to Samson, 1 run, another single. Not hurting LSG for sure. Went off the leading edge and past cover. The batter wanted to turn it away but got a leading edge
Krunal Pandya to Dhruv Jurel, no run, nudges the ball down and the bowler stops it to his right
Krunal Pandya to Dhruv Jurel, no run, quicker one, punched back to the bowler
Krunal Pandya to Dhruv Jurel, no run, five dots for Dhruv Jurel! Quicker one, punched to the man at cover
Krunal Pandya to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, angled in, tucked down to long-on for a single. He is finally off the mark
Krunal Pandya to Samson, 1 run, one more run. Angled in and tucked down to deep mid for a single
Mishra to Samson, 1 run, googly and Samson goes back to punch it down to deep cover for a single
Mishra to Dhruv Jurel, SIX, infuses enough power into the shot and lofts it over long-on. Was a tossed up delivery wide outside off and Dhruv Jurel hit it really well
Mishra to Dhruv Jurel, no run, quicker one, pushed back to the bowler
Mishra to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, punches it down to long-on for a single by waiting on it
Mishra to Samson, FOUR, bad ball! Quicker one, down leg, Samson laps it fine and sends it past the dive of the man at short fine. Four added to the tally
Mishra to Samson, no run, dot ball to end the over. Not a great over from Mishra. Was well tossed up and Samson drove it sans much timing to find cover
Yash Thakur [1.0-0-10-1] is back into the attack
Yash Thakur to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, the pacer back into the attack. Thought, Bishnoi might get a look in. Was a fuller one, squeezed down to third man for a single
Yash Thakur to Samson, 1 run, low full toss, outside off, might have slipped out and Samson lost his shape trying to hit it too hard. Only a single to long-off

Yash Thakur to Dhruv Jurel, FOUR, creamed through the off-side for a four! Was a fuller ball, outside off, Dhruv Jurel got under it and lofted it over cover. He managed to get under it and then just went through. Important four
Yash Thakur to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, low full toss, outside off, cue-ended down to long-off for a single. The 100 is up for RR

Yash Thakur to Samson, FOUR, straight down the ground for a four! He hit that so well. The umpire went out of harm's way as the low full toss was slammed back past the bowler. I don't think the move to bring back Yash has been a good one so far
Yash Thakur to Samson, wide, fuller length, well wide, outside off, left alone and has been wided. The wide yorker ploy just hasn't worked in this over. The spinners weren't doing that bad a job
Yash Thakur to Samson, wide, very full, little slower, Samson bailed out and has been wided

Yash Thakur to Samson, FOUR, big over for RR and they would be elated. Length delivery, well wide outside off and Samson stayed his crease to slam it between long-off and deep cover. That was timed and placed well by Samson. I0$
Krunal Pandya [2.0-0-10-0] is back into the attack
Krunal Pandya to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, change of ends for Krunal. Flatter one, nudged down to deep mid for a single
Krunal Pandya to Samson, 1 run, dances down, looks to go inside out and gets an inside edge. They eke out a single. The ball was bowled very slowly by Krunal Pandya
Krunal Pandya to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, drives a fuller one down to long-on for a single as that was at the sticks
Krunal Pandya to Samson, 1 run, on the pads, whipped down to deep square for a single. Was a quicker one
Krunal Pandya to Dhruv Jurel, no run, quicker one, angled in, Dhruv Jurel misses the tuck. There was an appeal but they don't review
Krunal Pandya to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, tucks a flatter one down to deep mid for a single. Excellent over again from Krunal despite bowling from a different end
RR need 82 off 42 balls.
Mohsin Khan [2.0-0-16-0] is back into the attack

Mohsin Khan to Dhruv Jurel, FOUR, the pacers aren't doing a great job! Four to start a fresh over. Was a short and wide ball. Dhruv Jurel stood tall and punched it between deep third and deep cover. He placed it so well. The timing was serene as well
Mohsin Khan to Dhruv Jurel, SIX, walks across a fuller ball and laps it over deep fine. Waited on it and used the pace of the bowler. Excellent batting this from Dhruv Jurel

Mohsin Khan to Dhruv Jurel, FOUR, fifty for the duo! Jurel, the jewel is turning it on. Was a short of length delivery and Dhruv Jurel pivots on the back foot to pull it past deep square for a four. His placement has been impeccable. The square leg fielder was in and Dhruv Jurel picked the gap

Mohsin Khan to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, 15 off the over already and a dropped catch now! The man at short third - Thakur - drops it. Fuller, wider, Dhruv Jurel reached out for it and sliced it. The ball flew off the edge and the fielder leapt up but failed to pouch it. I0$
Mohsin Khan to Samson, 1 run, length delivery, well outside off and Samson slaps it down to deep cover for a single

Mohsin Khan to Dhruv Jurel, FOUR, excellent effort! Half chance but Thakur fails to grab it again. The batter poked at a back of a length delivery and the ball flew off the edge. The man at short third flew to his left but failed to hold on to it. The ball then ricocheted away for a four. 20 runs off the over and the RR team needs 10 an over from here on
Krunal Pandya [3.0-0-15-0] is back into the attack

Over Summary 7-14 > Stoinis strikes off his first ball. Jaiswal departs > Amit Mishra comes on as impact sub, gets the wicket of Parag > Jurel and Samson resurrect the innings > Jurel leads the attack, gets three fours and a six off Mohsin Khan > 62 needed off the last 6 overs.
Krunal Pandya to Samson, 1 run, dances down and stabs it down to deep cover for a single
Krunal Pandya to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, quicker one, outside off, slapped down to long-off for a single

Krunal Pandya to Samson, FOUR, wow! This is the shot of the evening! That was a flatter one on the pads and reverse slapped it over point. Some winderful hands from the skipper. He has been in great form
Krunal Pandya to Samson, 1 run, gets that down to long-off for a single
Krunal Pandya to Dhruv Jurel, no run, quicker one, angled in, Dhruv Jurel fails to wood it
Krunal Pandya to Dhruv Jurel, 2 runs, dances down, tucks it away into the gap for a brace. Was well placed indeed by Dhruv Jurel. Krunal has finished an impressive spell
Ravi Bishnoi, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack

Ravi Bishnoi to Samson, 1 run, flatter one, spins in, a little, Samson looks to pull and loses his bat in the process. Slippery sweaty hands I reckon. Mistimed the shot down to deep backward for a single
Ravi Bishnoi to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, flogs it across the line for a single as the ball angled in
Ravi Bishnoi to Samson, FOUR, quicker one, angled in, Samson went for the slog and managed to send it wide of the man at deep mid. That went well into the gap and RR add four more
Ravi Bishnoi to Samson, FOUR, Samson is bossing the chase now. Stood tall, upright, got under the ball and lofted it over cover. He is batting so well and seeing the ball like a beach ball
Ravi Bishnoi to Samson, no run, dot ball! LSG need plenty of these. Quicker one, well outside off and slapped back to the bowler

Ravi Bishnoi to Samson, SIX, the man at deep mid did back track but it was Jonty Rhodes beyond the fence who caught it. Was a short ball, angled in and Samson stayed low to slam the pull. The fielder for a second was in contention but the ball eventually went over him. Big over again and RR making the right noise as the crowd at Ekana goes silent. 37 needed off the last 4 overs and by 2024 IPL standards, it should be a dawdle

Time-out. RR well ahead. They had a few hiccups. But Jurel first and then Samson have managed to find the gaps at will to keep the rate at check. Bishnoi was brought into the attack very late and was taken to the cleaners by Samson. LSG's plans in the last few overs have been poor.
Yash Thakur [2.0-0-27-1] is back into the attack
Yash Thakur to Dhruv Jurel, 2 runs, fuller ball, whipped wide of long-on and they steal a couple more. Poor fielding as that shouldn't have been a duo of runs
Yash Thakur to Dhruv Jurel, no run, short, little closer to the body, dabbed down to the man at short third man
Yash Thakur to Dhruv Jurel, FOUR, short ball, angled in, pulled down into the gap for a four. Was superbly placed indeed
Yash Thakur to Dhruv Jurel, 2 runs, fuller length delivery, Dhruv Jurel clips the ball away and wide of deep mid for a brace
Yash Thakur to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, short ball, Dhruv Jurel gets on top of the bounce and pulls it down to deep mid for a single
Yash Thakur to Samson, 1 run, short ball, Samson gets on top of the bounce and pulls it down to deep fine for a single. 27 needed off the last three overs
Mohsin Khan [3.0-0-36-0] is back into the attack
Mohsin Khan to Samson, 2 runs, length delivery, wide outside off, Samson slaps it wide of long-off for a brace

Mohsin Khan to Samson, no run, Jurel has had a date with lady luck for sure. That was steered down to short third. Thakur fumbled and then threw it to the bowler who fumbled and let Dhruv Jurel to come back into the crease. This is poor from LSG. The throw from Thakur also wasn't a great one but Mohsin Khan certainly could have done better
Mohsin Khan to Samson, SIX, fifty for Samson! That was a short ball, Samson got on top of the bounce and slammed it over deep mid. Huge hit inndeed. The skipper has continued his good form
Mohsin Khan to Samson, 1 run, gets it down to deep mid for a single

Mohsin Khan to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, fifty for Jurel. Put it away on to the on-side with elan. Jurel has had a charmed life but has done well to get the runs away. He would ideally want to finish it off now. The 'Salute' celebration comes out. This kid has a bright future indeed
Mohsin Khan to Samson, SIX, on the pads, Samson whips it and sends it over deep mid. The fielder in the deep was again interested but went over him. Samson wants to finish it off in a hurry now
Yash Thakur to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, short ball, Dhruv Jurel gets on top of the bounce and pulls it down to fine leg for a single
Yash Thakur to Samson, 1 run, one more. 10 needed now. Very full, Samson got the bat down and squeezed it down to third man for a single
Yash Thakur to Dhruv Jurel, no run, length delivery, outside off, keeps a little low, cue-ended down to mid-wicket
Yash Thakur to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, low full toss, Dhruv Jurel loses his shape and mistimes it down to long leg for a single

Yash Thakur to Samson, FOUR, four more. Only 4 needed now. Can't bowl short to this dynamite. He was hanging back and hammered it off the back foot and over mid-wicket for a four. RR only one shot away now

Yash Thakur to Samson, SIX, low full toss, dipping on the pads, Samson whips it over fine leg and RR win by 7 wickets. Huge hit and the skipper finishes it off in style. A wicket-keeper doing so is a fancy thing in India. Samson and RR are almost through to the top four. They have 16 points from 9 games already

23:10 Local Time, 17:40 GMT, 23:10 IST: RR win again! Yawn. They are making it look so easy. Have we travelled back to 2008? Their skipper at the forefront of it. Samson led from the front with the bat and stayed till the end to score 71 off 33 balls. He rarely put a foot wrong. Jurel at the other end played a few fancy shots but got a few chances and notched up his fifty. The LSG team didn't have the plans in place once these two got going and looked a little out of ideas. Someone as good as Bishnoi ended up bowling only one over. This after LSG fought back towards the end of the powerplay when they picked up three wickets for a few runs. Buttler and Jaiswal started off on fast lanes which eased the pressure at the start. But post the three wickets that went down, Samson and Dhruv Jurel took charge. LSG with their batting efforts had Rahul and Hooda laying the platform for them. They managed 196 and it was a very decent score.

But Rahul and men got it wrong with their bowling moves. They introduced Amit Mishra as their impact player and he delivered as well in his first over. But he went for a few runs in his second. That in a way delayed the entry point of Bishnoi who ended up bowling only one over. Krunal at the other end however was very accurate and gave away only 24 in his four overs. The pacers - Yash Thakur and Mohsin - looked very clueless and gave away plenty of runs. Thakur's second over started off the assault for RR who found pace easy to deal with at that point of time. LSG despite the loss are still at fourth on the table.

KL Rahul | LSG captain: I think we left about 20 runs behind. We didn’t get an ideal start but with the partnership me and Hooda had was great. In these sorts of games, the set batter had to score close to a hundred after getting to 50-60. I think we were 150 after about 15 overs, should have capitalized on it a bit more. I think it is clear the team with more sixes ends up winning. We do try to hit our sixes but today we had to change our approach after those two early wicket. If Hooda pushed on and scored 20 more, and I got 20 more then we’d finish around 220. That would have been the difference, that’s the 20 runs we left behind. We’re seeing with every game how important it is to give the bowlers that extra cushion because they are under the pump. Everyone loves range hitting and hitting it all over the park, we are no different. It is part of the prep. Our big hitters are Stoin and Pooran who can hit those big shots. The other guys like us try to pick our areas and time the shots better. (On Mishra and Bishnoi) There is a bit of chat before the game with the numbers and how opposition players match-up. Mishra is an experienced player and today was a day we knew he could be useful with how slow he bowls and with the larger boundaries. Once the runs kept flowing, they put pressure on our bowlers. There were 2-3 overs when Krunal bowled really well and squeezed them but then they attacked the fast bowlers. I couldn’t get a good time to get Bishnoi, wanted to keep him for the backend when Rovman and Hetmyer came out to bat because we know he can bowl well to them.

Dhruv Jurel - I just wanted to finish the match whenever I got a chance ( during batting). It's always a blessing / curse (playing in the middle-order), I just wanted to stay until the end and finish the game for my team. I will have to practice, in the batting PP, you have just two fielders outrside the ring, during the middle-overs, you'll need to find the gaps and get the big hits going as there are 5 fielders in thew deep, that's what I was looking at. I started well, but my shots went straight to the fielders. Sanju then told me to calm down, don't go too hard, take my time and then I got 20 runs in an over and that got me going. I always play for my papa, I did so during the Test match as well. he was then in the army, he was there today and that was for him (on the salute celebrations)

LSG defending totals in the IPL \n2022 and 2023: 15 matches, 12 wins, two defeats, 1 NR \n2024: 6 matches, three wins, three defeats

Sanju Samson, Player of the Match: I am very lucky to be behind the wickets. There was some purchase with the new ball and then was a good wicket to bat on. The guys who came in and bowl one over in the power-play do an important job. There has been a lot of planning behind the scenes. The start and the end of the innings was good. We gave away a few in the middle overs. Form is temporary in this format. We have seen Jurel in Tests. We believe in him. He has been batting one hour and two hours at times in the nets. We have been doing really well. We have been a little lucky as well. We need to keep the process right. At the team meetings, we talk about ticking the processes. One game at a time for us.

RR have been a seamless in their performances. They have been running on auto mode. Opponents on the road have failed to stop them. One of those rare teams who have been superb away from home. LSG came into this on the back of two excellent wins against CSK but they have been stopped. And that too at home. RR with this win have booked one of the top four places for sure. And they still have five more games to go. Speaks volumes about their dominance. Remember, they were finalists in 2022 as well. But given their form in this edition, that one final step might happen! LSG have made it two play-offs and they still look good for another one. But they will have to brush up their execution a little and comeback stronger next time. We will comeback again as well. But our team of Pradeep Krishnamurthy, Saurabh Shankar, Siva and Kumar Abhisekh Das wishes you good bye for the day! Ciao...
